                            <comment id="14182221" author="csun" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 00:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are two problems I found:&lt;br/&gt;
1. one thread may be reused for multiple queries, and therefore, if one &lt;tt&gt;IOContext&lt;/tt&gt; is bound to one thread, and the &lt;tt&gt;IOContext&lt;/tt&gt; is not initialized, we need to clear it when we close the map record handler;&lt;br/&gt;
2. synchronization is needed - the thread who doesn&apos;t have &lt;tt&gt;IOContext&lt;/tt&gt; initialized may try to retrieve before the thread who have &lt;tt&gt;IOContext&lt;/tt&gt; initialized saving it. Right now, a thread will save &lt;tt&gt;IOContext&lt;/tt&gt; right after initializing it. But, this is not a perfect solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14182222" author="csun" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2014 00:07:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch also enables caching on input RDD, so once this is resolved, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-8437&quot; title=&quot;Modify SparkPlan generation to set toCache flag to SparkTrans where caching is needed [Spark Branch]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-8437&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-8437&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should also be resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
